HEADWORD: Foremast
<hw>Fore"mast`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The mast nearest the bow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Foremast hand</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Foremast man</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a common
sailor; also, a man stationed to attend to the gear of the
foremast.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foremeant</ent>⟦br⟧
